<task id="021" project="ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>C2 — Migrate prompts from .txt files into sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-date>2026-06-02</completed-date>
    <wave>C</wave>
    <estimated-effort>1d</estimated-effort>
    <tags>prompt-migration, sprk_analysisaction, dataverse, retire-txt-files</tags>
    <dependencies>013</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <wave-item>C2</wave-item>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate Phase 1 prompt content from .txt files in Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/ into the JPS-formatted sprk_systemprompt field on the corresponding sprk_analysisaction rows (per A4 design — no new entity). Then delete the .txt files. This is the load-bearing acceptance step for SC-08 (zero .txt prompt files) and FR-06 (SMEs can edit prompts without a code deploy).
  </prompt>

  <role>Prompt curator + Dataverse data migration specialist.</role>

  <goal>
    Three Phase 1 prompts (classification.v1.txt, outcome-extraction.v1.txt, predict-matter-cost-synthesis.v1.txt) migrated into JPS-formatted sprk_systemprompt JSON on the matching sprk_analysisaction rows. Phase 1.5 ingest action rows (Wave B1 + C1) similarly carry their canonical prompts. .txt files deleted from source. Code that loaded .txt files updated to read from Dataverse (likely already does via existing sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt load — verify).
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="r1-prompts">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/*.txt (3 files)</file>
    <file purpose="a4-design">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-a4-prompt-variants.md (from task 013)</file>
    <file purpose="wave-b-actions">Spaarke Dev sprk_analysisaction rows from Wave B1</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md SC-08">Zero .txt prompt files in Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/ after this task</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-02">All prompt content lives in sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt (or per-playbook sprk_configjson)</constraint>
    <constraint source="A4">Use the variant/versioning pattern decided in A4 design</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Audit existing .txt prompts">Confirm all 3 files + their consumers (which actions load them)</step>
    <step order="2" name="Wrap .txt content in JPS schema">For each prompt, construct sprk_systemprompt JSON ($schema, $version, instruction { role, task, constraints, context }, input, parameters) per A4 pattern</step>
    <step order="3" name="Update or create sprk_analysisaction rows">For Phase 1 Layer 1, Layer 2, synthesis actions — populate or update sprk_systemprompt</step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify code path reads from Dataverse">Trace BFF prompt-loading code; if it currently reads .txt, refactor to read sprk_systemprompt</step>
    <step order="5" name="Smoke test">Re-run predict-matter-cost end-to-end (similar to Wave B5) and confirm same Inference output (no behavior regression)</step>
    <step order="6" name="Delete .txt files">git rm of the 3 files</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update DI / config">Remove any prompt-file path config no longer needed</step>
    <step order="8" name="Quality gates">code-review + adr-check + side-by-side prompt comparison (manual)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__update_record">Update sprk_systemprompt</tool>
    <tool name="git">Delete files + commit</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse-data">sprk_systemprompt populated on 3+ existing/new action rows</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/*.txt DELETED</output>
    <output type="code">Prompt-loading code updated to read sprk_systemprompt (if not already)</output>
    <output type="test">Behavior parity smoke test results</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero .txt files in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All Phase 1 prompts present in sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt rows</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">predict-matter-cost smoke test (post-migration) produces same Inference output as pre-migration on the same fixture matter</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No regressions in build / tests</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <completion-summary>
Wave C2 task 021 completed 2026-06-02. 3 Phase 1 prompts migrated from .txt files into Dataverse sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt JPS-formatted JSON: classification.v1.txt → NEW INS-L1C row; outcome-extraction.v1.txt → NEW INS-L2X row; predict-matter-cost-synthesis.v1.txt → EXISTING INS-AGNT row (placeholder JPS replaced with full content). Also created 2 sibling NEW rows reserved by Wave C1 deferred-deploy plan: INS-SANI (Sanitization), INS-OBSE (Observation Emit). Build verified: 0 errors, 15 pre-existing warnings (none introduced). Side-by-side comparison artifact authored at projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/notes/handoffs/c2-prompt-migration-comparison.md.

Acceptance criteria status:
- ⏳ Criterion 1 (zero .txt files in Prompts/) — DEFERRED to Wave C3 (task 022 IngestOrchestrator retirement). The .txt files are still actively read by IngestOrchestrator.RunLayer1Async/RunLayer2Async via IInsightsPromptLoader; deleting them in C2 would crash the live ingest path. Per task 022 dependency chain (022 depends on 020 + 023), C3 is the canonical retirement step. Reasoning fully documented in comparison artifact §5; recommendation to owner: reword criterion 1 to "prompt content migrated such that .txt files become unreferenced after Wave C3" OR move criterion 1 to task 022's acceptance criteria.
- ✅ Criterion 2 (all Phase 1 prompts present in sprk_systemprompt rows) — VERIFIED via Dataverse query at end of execution; all 12 INS-* rows active with JPS-formatted sprk_systemprompt (8 Wave B existing + 4 Wave C1 created in C2).
- ⏳ Criterion 3 (predict-matter-cost smoke test produces same Inference output) — DEFERRED because (a) Wave C2 did not change the live code path (still reads predict-matter-cost-synthesis.v1.txt via $ref: inline at deploy-time; INS-AGNT row update is for FR-06 SME-iterate surface, not yet wired as runtime source); (b) live smoke against spaarke-bff-dev requires owner-coordinated deploy window per bff-extensions §F.4 (BFF code unchanged in C2, so no BFF redeploy required — but smoke still needs Dataverse connectivity which the parallel project hold doesn't affect). Wave C4 (task 023 — facade rewire) is when the canonical consumption path switches.
- ✅ Criterion 4 (no regressions in build / tests) — VERIFIED via `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` → 0 errors, 15 pre-existing warnings (none introduced by C2). No code changes in this wave — Dataverse data-only migration.

Strategic gap surfaced: design-a4 §10 prescribes renaming 8 Wave B rows to `&lt;base&gt;@v1` suffix. EMPIRICALLY BLOCKED: sprk_actioncode has a 10-char max length (confirmed during C2 via test row `INS-TEST@v1` rejection with explicit validation error). All Insights rows treated as "v1 by convention"; future v2 requires schema MaxLength extension (Phase 2+). Filed as follow-up C2-FU-1 (design-a4 erratum) and C2-FU-5 (Phase 2+ schema change).
    </completion-summary>

